  "texts": [
    "(b) Part-of-Speech (POS) Tagging: In part-of-speech tagging, each token is assigned a part-of-speech tag that represents its grammatical role in the sentence.",
    "POS tags provide information about whether a word is a noun, verb, adjective, etc., which can help in identifying named entities [29], [52], [53], [54], [55].",
    "For example, in the sentence \"John works at Google,\" the word \"John\" would be tagged as a proper noun, while \"Google\" would be tagged as a noun.",
    "(c) Named Entity Recognition (NER): Using various techniques, the NER model analyzes the tokens and their corresponding POS tags to identify named entities in the text.",
    "NER also examines patterns, contextual information, and linguistic features to determine the boundaries and types of entities present [49], [48]."
  ],
